- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new method for tetrahedral meshing, which is a topic within computational geometry.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as tetrahedral meshing is commonly used in computer graphics applications such as finite element analysis and physics simulations.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the algorithmic approach used in the proposed method.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper deals with the conversion of rational numbers to floating-point numbers, which is a topic within numerical analysis.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as tetrahedral meshing is used in 3D modeling and animation, which are topics within multimedia.
